column4:
Can/Rev Indicator Establishes if the transaction is a cancel, offset, or rebill. Allowable values are: 
CAN - Transaction has been canceled before verification.
CXL - Transaction has been revised or canceled after verification. 
CXR - Transaction is a rebill of an original transaction and the rebill itself has been revised or canceled. 
OFF - Transaction is an offset of an original transaction that has been revised or canceled. 
OFR - Transaction is an offset of a rebill that has been revised or canceled. 
RBL - Transaction is a rebill of an original transaction that has been revised.
RTN - This value indicates that a piece of collateral has been returned during the term of a deal
Include only revised or blank indicator. Ignore Canceled and Offsets
